53 12-3-713.
54 (a) There is established the Vince Dooley Battlefield Trust Fund Program to be
55 administered by the department. In administering the program, the department shall, each
56 fiscal year, make available moneys from the Vince Dooley Battlefield Trust Fund for
57 matching grants to any organization having a project proposal which has been reviewed
58 and approved by the department.
59 (b) The department shall make available moneys from the fund solely for the purpose of
60 awarding grants to organizations for the fee simple purchase of, or purchase of permanent
61 protective interests in, any Georgia battlefield listed in the following reports:
62 (1) The Report on the Nation's Civil War Battlefields by the Civil War Sites Advisory
63 Commission (Civil War Sites Advisory Commission/National Parks Service, 1993, as
64 amended); or
