65 (2) The Report to Congress on the Historic Preservation of Revolutionary War and War
66 of 1812 Sites in the United States by the American Battlefield Protection Program of the
67 National Park Service (United States Department of the Interior/National Park Service,
68 2007, as amended).
69 (c) Organizations seeking grant funding shall be required to provide at least $1.00 in
70 matching contributions for each $1.00 received from the fund for the project proposal. No
71 state funds shall be included in determining the amount of such matching contributions.
72 (d) Grants from the fund shall not exceed 50 percent of the appraised value of the land or
73 permanent protective interest therein.
74 (e) Grants from the fund may be awarded for prospective purchases or for acquisitions on
75 which the applicant has closed. In the latter case, the applicant shall demonstrate that:
76 (1) The closing occurred no more than 12 months prior to the date of application for the
77 grant; and
78 (2) An identifiable threat to the resource or compelling need for preservation existed at
79 the time of the purchase.
80 12-3-714.
81 The department shall establish guidelines for applications, evaluations, and awards from
82 the fund in consultation with relevant battlefield preservation interests. In awarding grants,
83 the department shall give primary consideration to the following factors:
84 (1) Significance of the battlefield that is the subject of the project proposal;
85 (2) Degree to which the property or interest therein to be acquired falls within the core
86 and study areas of the battlefield, as described in the relevant report of the American
87 Battlefield Protection Program;
88 (3) Proximity of the property to other protected lands;
89 (4) Threats to the integrity of features associated with the relevant battle;
90 (5) The financial capacity of the applicant to complete the project; and
