95 (a) Any organization making an acquisition of property or interest therein pursuant to this
96 article shall grant to the department or other holder a perpetual conservation easement
97 placing restrictions on the use or development of the property. In cases where the easement
98 is granted to a holder other than the department, all terms and conditions of the easement
99 shall accomplish the perpetual preservation of the property. Such other holder shall
100 demonstrate to the department that it has the capacity and expertise to manage and enforce
101 the terms of the easement.
102 (b) Nothing in this Code section shall preclude the subsequent transfer or assignment by
103 a state agency or other holder of any property interest acquired pursuant to this article to
104 the United States of America to be incorporated into a national park, national forest,
105 national wildlife refuge, or other national conservation area in accordance with
106 54 U.S.C. Section 10010, 16 U.S.C. Section 551, the Fish and Wildlife Act of 1956 (16
107 U.S.C. Section 742a et seq.), or 16 U.S.C. Section 1131, as amended and applicable. The
108 department shall facilitate transfers and assignments of any such interests."
